description: ORDER ON MOTION TO STRIKE CLASS ALLEGATION AND MOTIONS TO DISMISS (Dkt.  21 ,  22 ,  78 ).  The Court finds and ORDERS: Defendants' Motion to Strike Class Allegations (Dkt.  21 ) is GRANTED IN PART AND DENIED IN PART; Defendants' Motion to  Dismiss (Dkt.  22 ) is GRANTED IN PART AND DENIED IN PART;  Defendants' Renewed Motion to Dismiss for Lack of Standing (Dkt.  78 ) is GRANTED; Plaintiffs' Motion to Seal (Dkt.  93 ) is GRANTED; Plaintiffs' Claims 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 9 , 10, 11, 12, 13, and 14 of the Second Amended Complaint (Dkt.  19 ) are DISMISSED. Plaintiffs are not permitted leave to amend the complaint. As there is only one remaining state law claim (Claim 6), Plaintiffs are ORDERED to show cause no later than 3/25/2024 why this matter should not be dismissed for lack of subject matter jurisdiction.    Signed  by U.S. District Judge David G Estudillo.(AMD)
